INPUT - A array of size 'n' is given.
OUTPUT - Find the sum of contiguous subarray within a array of numbers which has the largest sum.
SUMMARY - The main idea of Kadaneâ€™s algorithm is to look for all positive contiguous segments of the array. 
          And keep track of maximum sum contiguous segment among all positive segments.

# Input List
nums = list(map(int,input().split(" ")))
maxi = nums[0]
max_so_far = nums[0]
starting = ending = s = 0
for i in range(1,len(nums)):
    max_so_far = max(nums[i],max_so_far+nums[i])
    if max_so_far > maxi:
        maxi = max_so_far
        starting = s
        ending = i
    else:
        s += 1
print(maxi)
print(starting, ending)

Complexity:
Time - O(n)
Space - O(1)
